AgentForce Infotech AWS Resources and Access

## Getting AWS Access

1. Request through AgentForce IT Service Portal: https://itportal.agentforce.internal
2. Select "AWS Access Request" form
3. Specify required AWS services (EC2, S3, RDS, Lambda, etc.)
4. Get manager approval (required)
5. Complete AWS security training (mandatory, 30-minute course)
6. Receive IAM credentials within 48 hours via encrypted email from aws-admin@agentforce.com

AWS Security Training: https://training.agentforce.com/aws-security

## Account Structure

AgentForce uses AWS Organizations with three accounts:

- **Development Account (agentforce-dev)**: 
  - For local testing and dev environments
  - Account ID: 123456789012
  - Less restrictive policies
  
- **Staging Account (agentforce-staging)**: 
  - Pre-production testing
  - Account ID: 234567890123
  - Production-like environment
  
- **Production Account (agentforce-prod)**: 
  - Live services (highly restricted access)
  - Account ID: 345678901234
  - Requires additional approval and 2FA

## Common Services

**EC2 Instances**
- Development: Use t3.medium or t3.large instances
- Staging: t3.large or m5.large
- Production: Auto-scaling groups with m5.xlarge instances
- Tag all resources: `Project: Phoenix`, `Environment: dev/staging/prod`, `Owner: {your-email}`

**S3 Buckets**
- Development: `s3://agentforce-dev-{project}-{purpose}/`
- Staging: `s3://agentforce-staging-{project}-{purpose}/`
- Production: `s3://agentforce-prod-{project}-{purpose}/`
- All buckets have versioning and encryption enabled

**RDS Databases (PostgreSQL)**
- Managed by DevOps team (Anjali Mehta)
- Request access through IT portal
- Use read replicas for reporting queries
- Automated backups enabled (7-day retention)

**Lambda Functions**
- Deploy via GitLab CI/CD pipeline
- Monitor in CloudWatch (dashboards in Grafana)
- Set appropriate timeouts (max 15 minutes)
- Use environment variables for configuration

**EKS (Kubernetes)**
- Production Kubernetes cluster managed by DevOps
- Access via kubectl (configure with AWS CLI)
- Contact Anjali Mehta for cluster access

## Cost Management

- Review AWS costs monthly (FinOps dashboard: https://finops.agentforce.internal)
- Use Reserved Instances for production (managed by DevOps)
- Tag all resources for cost allocation (required)
- Shut down unused dev resources (automated cleanup runs weekly)
- Contact FinOps team (finops@agentforce.com) for cost optimization

Cost alerts: Set up in AWS Cost Explorer (contact Anjali Mehta)

## Security

- Use IAM roles (not access keys) for applications
- Enable MFA for AWS Console access (mandatory)
- Follow principle of least privilege
- Review IAM policies quarterly (Security team audits)
- Never commit AWS credentials to GitLab
- Use AWS Secrets Manager for sensitive data
- All S3 buckets have encryption (SSE-S3 or SSE-KMS)

## Monitoring

- **CloudWatch**: Metrics and logs
  - Dashboard: https://console.aws.amazon.com/cloudwatch
  - Alarms configured for critical metrics
  
- **Grafana**: Aggregated monitoring
  - URL: https://grafana.agentforce.internal
  - AWS data sources configured
  
- **AWS Cost Explorer**: Cost analysis
  - URL: https://console.aws.amazon.com/cost-management
  - Monthly reports sent to managers

## AWS Console Access

- Development: https://agentforce-dev.signin.aws.amazon.com/console
- Staging: https://agentforce-staging.signin.aws.amazon.com/console
- Production: https://agentforce-prod.signin.aws.amazon.com/console

**Note**: Production console access requires additional approval and security clearance.

